Blood Pressure App
Effective Date: 01 July 2024
Your Privacy Matters
At Measurement Log: BP App, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information when you use our Blood Pressure Android application.
What Information Do We Collect?
When you use our app, we may collect the following information:
Email address
Username
Age
Gender
Weight and height
If you choose to sign in using a third-party platform like Google, we may also collect your account name, email, and public profile information.
We also automatically collect certain technical information about your device, such as the device type, operating system, and app usage data to help us improve the app.
Medical Disclaimer:
Our app is intended for informational purposes only and is not a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Always seek the advice of your physician or other qualified health provider with any questions you may have regarding a medical condition.
How Do We Use Your Information?
We use the information we collect to:
Provide and improve our app services
Analyze usage trends and statistics to enhance the app
Communicate with you about the app and respond to your requests
We will never use your personal information for marketing or share it with third parties for commercial purposes without your consent. The only exception is if we are required to disclose information to comply with legal obligations.
How Do We Protect Your Data?
We take data security seriously and use industry-standard practices to safeguard your information during transmission and storage. However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute protection.
Your Data Rights
As our user, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:
Right to access your information
Right to correct inaccurate or incomplete data
Right to withdraw consent for data processing
Right to request deletion of your data in certain cases
If you have any questions or wish to exercise these rights, please contact us at
tannerbrookstanner@gmail.com
Keeping Your Data Safe
We use up-to-date security measures to protect your information during transmission and storage. However, no method is completely secure so we cannot guarantee the protection of your data. We only keep analytics data for operating purposes and delete it regularly. Your personal details are deleted when you uninstall the app.
External Links and Age Restriction
Our app may contain links to external websites, which have their own privacy policies that apply. Our app is intended for users aged 13 and above. If you believe a minor has provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can delete it. Below is external links for further reference.
Google Play Services
AdMob
Meta Audience Network
Firebase Analytics
Permissions Required to Use Measurement Log: BP App
We may ask for necessary permissions to use our application. If you don’t give consent for these permissions, it may happen that you cannot use our application properly. We never use these permissions for personal use or to collect data. These permissions are a part of our application’s features.
Internet Permission
– This permission helps to upload or export your data (generated through our application) to online storage like your Google Drive or any other cloud services that our application supports.
Updates to the Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on our app. We encourage you to review the policy periodically for the most current information.
Thank you for using Measurement Log: BP App! If you have any privacy concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out to us at
tannerbrookstanner@gmail.com
